content:
The retirement of versions 21.0 through 30.0 of the Salesforce Platform API was first scheduled for Summer ’23, but is now postponed to Summer ’25. You can continue to use these API versions, but they’re not supported and won’t be available starting in Summer ’25. Applications consuming them are then disrupted.

Where: This change affects:

* Bulk API (21.0-30.0)
* SOAP API (21.0-30.0)
* REST API (v21.0-v30.0)

This also applies to all REST APIs that use URIs beneath /services/data/vXX.X/, including:

* Connect REST API
* IoT REST API
* Lightning Platform REST API
* Metadata API
* Place Order REST API
* Reports and Dashboards REST API
* Tableau CRM REST API
* Tooling API

This change applies to Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions.

How: Before the Summer ’25 release, modify or upgrade all applications to function with current API versions.
title: Salesforce Summer '24 Release Notes
